        "content": "\n**Untested:** `cmd_db_new` (first-run window vs. marker-based, `--limit` truncation at group boundaries, `groupby` batching logic), `cmd_db_mark` (`--now` vs explicit watermark vs. invalid ISO string vs. neither given), `_normalize_ats` (all 14 replacement rules, and the \"skip inside tags/style/script\" invariant), `_chrome_bin` (env override, `PATH` lookup, hardcoded app paths, none-found → `sys.exit`), `cmd_pdf_render` (missing input file, successful render, failed render — non-`%PDF` output), `run_claude`/`main`'s argv parsing (bare invocation → interactive, mode words vs. flags split).\n\n**Highest-value gaps:**\n- `_normalize_ats` correctness inside `<style>`/`<script>` tags — the whole point of that function is *not* mangling markup, and it's currently unverified.\n- `cmd_db_new`'s truncation-at-group-boundary logic (`if jobs and len(jobs) + len(g) > a.limit: truncated = True; break`) — subtle off-by-one-prone code, no test.\n- `cmd_db_mark` rejecting a malformed watermark (`return 2`).\n\n```python\n",
